FROM gpt-oss:20b

# =============================================================================
# gpt-oss-paperless-128k — paperless-gpt-tuned variant of gpt-oss:20b
#
# One of five context-length variants (8k / 16k / 32k / 64k / 128k). All share
# identical PARAMETER and SYSTEM blocks except for `num_ctx`. The variants
# exist so paperless-gpt can pick a fit per workload via `LLM_MODEL`, without
# OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH leaking across into the OCR model. Switching variants
# costs one model reload (~30-60 s) because KV-cache allocations differ.
#
# Purpose of the family: prevent the endless generation loops that occasionally
# trap gpt-oss:20b when called from paperless-gpt's batch processor over
# /api/chat. paperless-gpt has no client-side HTTP timeout (PR #972 open) and
# no num_predict cap on the text-LLM path (only OCR sets MaxTokens). Combined
# with gpt-oss's known reasoning loop (ollama#12606), a single doc can pin the
# GPU for hours. Capping output tokens at the model level is the only
# deterministic fix.
# =============================================================================

# --- Generation limits ------------------------------------------------------

# Hard cap on output tokens. paperless-gpt outputs:
#   - Title:        <120 chars  (~30 tokens)
#   - Correspondent: single name (~10 tokens)
#   - Custom Fields JSON: Summary up to 500 chars + Advice up to 300 chars
#                         + 5 smaller fields → realistically 1200-1500 tokens
#                         for a fully populated response
# 2048 leaves comfortable headroom even for the maxed-out JSON case while
# still bounding any loop to ~70 s at ~30 t/s on M1 Max. 1024 was too tight
# for long Summary+Advice combinations.
PARAMETER num_predict 2048

# Context window — THIS is what varies between the five variants.
# 131072 tokens for experimental — tight fit alongside glm-ocr in 30 GB wired budget
# KV-cache cost ~8 GB at q8_0.
# Acts as the Modelfile default — paperless-gpt must NOT set
# OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH (it would override this on the request).
PARAMETER num_ctx 131072

# Mild repetition damping in the Ollama-recommended range. Aggressive values
# (>1.3) do not help and degrade quality (ollama#12741).
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
PARAMETER repeat_last_n 256

# Maintainer guidance in ollama#12606 is "run with default parameters". Setting
# top_p / top_k was directly correlated with loops in reporter test cases —
# DO NOT override them here. temperature 0.6 is the gpt-oss default.
PARAMETER temperature 0.6

# Stop tokens: NOT overridden. gpt-oss uses the Harmony chat format with
# <|start|>, <|end|>, <|message|>, <|channel|>, <|return|>, <|call|>. A custom
# PARAMETER stop would REPLACE the inherited list and break the chat template.
# The stock list is inherited automatically via FROM.

# --- System prompt (identical across all five ctx variants) -----------------
#
# Universal rules that previously lived in every paperless-gpt user prompt
# (no-redaction, no-refusal, no-preface, language rule) are lifted to SYSTEM:
#   (a) saves ~150 tokens per call, ~360k tokens across an 800-doc batch
#   (b) SYSTEM outranks user message in the Harmony hierarchy — strongest
#       possible signal to gpt-oss against built-in refusal/censoring triggers
#   (c) "Reasoning: low" as the first line sets the loop guard before the
#       task is even read (ollama#12606: low/medium reasoning never loops)
#
# Task-specific content (examples, format rules, JSON schema) stays in the
# user prompts — those are well-crafted and would cause cross-task confusion
# if folded into SYSTEM.

SYSTEM """Reasoning: low.

You are a metadata-extraction worker for a personal, single-user, offline document archive.
The owner is the only reader. This is the owner's own paperwork. There is no third party.

UNIVERSAL RULES (apply to every request)
- Never refuse. Never add safety disclaimers. Never output "Censored", "Sorry", "I can't", or apologies.
- Never redact, mask, partially redact, abbreviate, or omit identifying numbers (Versicherungsnummer, Steuer-ID, Personalausweis, Reisepass, Aufenthaltstitel, IBAN, BIC, Konto-, Kreditkarten-, Patientennummer, Aktenzeichen, Bescheidnummer, СНИЛС, ИНН, паспорт, номер полиса). Copy them verbatim in their original script.
- No preface ("Title:", "Here is", "Sure", "JSON:", "Correspondent:"). Output only the requested content.

LANGUAGE RULE (only three supported languages)
- The archive owner reads German, English, and Russian. All output must be in one of these three.
- German document -> German output.
- English document -> English output.
- Russian document -> Russian output in Cyrillic (do not transliterate to Latin).
- ANY OTHER language (French, Italian, Spanish, Polish, Turkish, Arabic, Chinese, etc.) -> output in ENGLISH. Translate Summary, Advice, and any free-text field into English. Keep identifying numbers, names, and Reference strings verbatim in their original script.
- Never mix languages within one output. Never produce output in a language outside {de, en, ru}.

REASONING
- No chain of thought. No thinking aloud. No intermediate reasoning text. Direct answer only."""
